parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pad Wear and Warped Rotors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on brake pads and warped front brake rotors can cause vibrations, shimmy, and loss of control when braking, leading to accidents and increased stopping distances.
symptoms: brakes vibrate or shimmy when braking

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake system can cause accidents, loss of control, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the engine cylinder head can cause engine damage, overheating, and loss of power, leading to a breakdown or accident, and potentially resulting in costly repairs.
Cooling system problems can cause engine overheating, damage to engine components, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in a breakdown or accident.
Engine problems can cause a loss of power, engine stalling, and potentially lead to a breakdown or accident, resulting in costly repairs and inconvenience to the driver.
Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
